DetailedDescription: A Vahetus Rune allows you to swap avatars with another player.
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

Description: The Dagger may be used once per game. If you choose to activate it, you will kill one randomly selected player that visits you that night. Activating the Dagger will not prevent you from being killed.

DetailedDescription: A Fjät Rune allows you to stalk a player at night to find out who they visit
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

Description: A Töfrar Rune allows you to check a whether a player uses Witch Craft or not. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: Tarot cards allow you to check a player and get back one of their tarot cards
You will be given two cards in the morning. One will be randomly selected from the player, the other will be randomly selected from a different player in the game

Description: An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
Magi's Circlets were crafted during the ancient Mage War. Wearing one will provide you with protection from other witchcraft uses, role-blocking any that visit you.
Manacles of Spite allow you to roleblock a player each night. If you do, you will also roleblock yourself.

DetailedDescription: A Vahetus Rune allows you to swap avatars with another player.
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

Description: The Dagger may be used once per game. If you choose to activate it, you will kill one randomly selected player that visits you that night. Activating the Dagger will not prevent you from being killed.

DetailedDescription: A Fjät Rune allows you to stalk a player at night to find out who they visit
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

Description: A Töfrar Rune allows you to check a whether a player uses Witch Craft or not. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: Tarot cards allow you to check a player and get back one of their tarot cards
You will be given two cards in the morning. One will be randomly selected from the player, the other will be randomly selected from a different player in the game

Description: An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
Magi's Circlets were crafted during the ancient Mage War. Wearing one will provide you with protection from other witchcraft uses, role-blocking any that visit you.
Manacles of Spite allow you to roleblock a player each night. If you do, you will also roleblock yourself.

Manacles of Spite allow you to roleblock a player each night. If you do, you will also roleblock yourself.

If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

A Töfrar Rune allows you to check a whether a player uses Witch Craft or not. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vahetus Rune allows you to swap avatars with another player.
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

Description: Magi's Circlets were crafted during the ancient Mage War. Wearing one will provide you with protection from other witchcraft uses, role-blocking any that visit you.
Manacles of Spite allow you to roleblock a player each night. If you do, you will also roleblock yourself.

A Töfrar Rune allows you to check a whether a player uses Witch Craft or not. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: Tarot cards allow you to check a player and get back one of their tarot cards
You will be given two cards in the morning. One will be randomly selected from the player, the other will be randomly selected from a different player in the game
A Fjät Rune allows you to stalk a player at night to find out who they visit
Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

I really enjoyed the Circlet mechanics, actually.  I'd hoped it would be a soft-Disruption Orb, but with more interesting consequences.  Like you can keep it, and protect yourself from intel, but if you hold it and people get blocked on you lots, then you are Sus.  Plus the Undead had to think very carefully about who held it, as it would prevent the Necro from getting them up again, and the Ghoul wouldn't be able to approach either if they still held the rune.
